message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper deals with developing a deep neural network approach for segmenting left atrium and pulmonary veins from intracardiac echocardiography (ICE) images. This involves leveraging a database of diagnostic images to supplement the less available interventional images. The paper uses 3D geometrical information provided by a position sensor embedded in the ICE catheter and 3D image appearance information from a set of computed tomography cardiac volumes. Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories are computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), medical imaging (cs.MED), and computational neuroscience (cs.NEURON).
